events.description: The NZX 50 index fell 39 points in morning trade on Thursday.

events.event_name: New Zealand Q4 Jobs Data Release
events.description: Release of unemployment and employment figures for the fourth quarter in New Zealand.
The S&P 500 and Nasdaq experienced declines overnight due to a tech sell-off.
The next meeting where interest rate decisions will be made.

facts.fact_text: The NZX 50 fell 39 points, or 0.3%, to 13,428 in morning trade.

evidences.evidence_text: The NZX 50 fell 39 points, or 0.3%, to 13,428 in morning trade on Thursday

facts.fact_text: New Zealand's unemployment rate rose to 5.4% in Q4.

evidences.evidence_text: The latest data showed the unemployment rate in New Zealand rose to 5.4% in Q4

facts.fact_text: Employment in New Zealand increased by 0.5% in Q4.

evidences.evidence_text: employment increased 0.5%, above estimates of 0.3% after being flat in Q3
Among early losers were Freightways Group (-1.7%)

claims.claim_text: The latest jobs data raised questions about whether the central bank will cut interest rates.

evidences.evidence_text: The latest figures raised questions over whether the central bank will cut interest rates at the upcoming meeting.

claims.claim_text: The NZX 50 decline was influenced by the performance of Wall Street.

evidences.evidence_text: The broader index tracked a fall on Wall Street’s S&P 500 and Nasdaq overnight

claims.claim_text: The tech stock sell-off on Wall Street is persistent.

evidences.evidence_text: amid a persistent tech stock sell-off
